<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="chromosome number">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Chromosome number.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 34 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Onopordum illyricum L. subsp. illyricum from c. da Rossillo (San Marco Argentano, Cosenza), 2 n = 34. Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.12.79031.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/623294" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="voucher specimen">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Voucher specimen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Italy. Calabria.</emphasis>
San Marco Argentano (Cosenza), c.da Rossillo (WGS84: 
<geoCoordinate degrees="39.61343" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="39.61343">39.61343N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="16.22801" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="16.22801">16.22801E</geoCoordinate>
), 16 August 2021, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L. Peruzzi</emphasis>
(seeds collected and deposited at the germplasm bank of the Department of Biology, University of Pisa; IPEN: IT-0-PI-2021-0419).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species occurs in southern Europe, from the Iberian Peninsula to the Balkans, in Turkey, and in Syria (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="3, Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Greuter, W, 2006. Compositae (pro parte majore). In: Greuter W, Raab-Straube E von (Eds) Compositae. Euro+Med Plantbase - the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity. [accessed 3 December 2021] https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" title="Compositae (pro parte majore). In: Greuter W, Raab-Straube E von (Eds) Compositae. Euro + Med Plantbase - the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity. [accessed 3 December 2021]" url="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" year="2006">Greuter 2006</bibRefCitation>
+). Although several chromosome counts are available in the literature (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" author="Moore, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="281 - 299" refId="B23" refString="Moore, RJ, Frankton, C, 1962. Cytotaxonomic studies in the tribe Cynareae (Compositae). Canadian Journal of Botany 40 (2): 281 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" title="Cytotaxonomic studies in the tribe Cynareae (Compositae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" volume="40" year="1962">Moore and Frankton 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chuksanova, NA" journalOrPublisher="Botanicheskii Zhurnal (Moscow and Leningrad)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="381 - 386" refId="B11" refString="Chuksanova, NA, Sveshnikova, LI, Alexandrova, TV, 1968. A new evidence on chromosome numbers in species of the family Compositae. Giseke. Botanicheskii Zhurnal (Moscow and Leningrad) 53: 381 - 386" title="A new evidence on chromosome numbers in species of the family Compositae. Giseke." volume="53" year="1968">Chuksanova et al. 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Valdes, B" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural, Seccion Biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="193 - 197" refId="B31" refString="Valdes, B, 1970. Numeros cromosomicos de algunas plantas espanolas. Boletin de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural, Seccion Biologica 68: 193 - 197" title="Numeros cromosomicos de algunas plantas espanolas." volume="68" year="1970">Valdes 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" author="Kuzmanov, B" editor="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon 28 (4)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="391 - 408" refId="B21" refString="Kuzmanov, B, Georgieva, S, Nikolova, M, 1979. Reports. In: Loeve, A, Ed., IOPB chromosome numbers reports LXIV. Taxon 28(4): 391 - 408, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" title="Reports." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" volumeTitle="IOPB chromosome numbers reports LXIV." year="1979">Kuzmanova et al. 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Snogerup, S" editor="Kamari, G" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="331 - 337" refId="B28" refString="Snogerup, S, 1995. Reports 491-517. In: Kamari, G, Felber, F, Garbari, F, Eds., Mediterranean chromosome number reports 5. Flora Mediterranea 5: 331 - 337" title="Reports 491 - 517." volume="5" volumeTitle="Mediterranean chromosome number reports 5." year="1995">Snogerup 1995</bibRefCitation>
), no data have been published so far for Italy, where two subspecies can be found, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. illyricum" genus="O." lsidName="O. illyricum subsp. illyricum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="subSpecies" species="illyricum" subSpecies="illyricum">O. illyricum subsp. illyricum</taxonomicName>
, distributed throughout south-central Italy (including Sardegna and Sicilia), and 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. illyricum subsp. cardunculus" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="subSpecies" species="illyricum" subSpecies="cardunculus">O. illyricum subsp. cardunculus</taxonomicName>
(Boiss.) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Arènes">Arenes</normalizedToken>
, which is known only for Sicilia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" author="Bartolucci, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="179 - 303" refId="B5" refString="Bartolucci, F, Peruzzi, L, Galasso, G, Albano, A, Alessandrini, A, Ardenghi, NMG, Astuti, G, Bacchetta, G, Ballelli, S, Banfi, E, Barberis, G, Bernardo, L, Bouvet, D, Bovio, M, Cecchi, L, Di Pietro, R, Domina, G, Fascetti, S, Fenu, G, Festi, F, Foggi, B, Gallo, L, Gottschlich, G, Gubellini, L, Iamonico, D, Iberite, M, Jimenez-Mejias, P, Lattanzi, E, Marchetti, D, Martinetto, E, Masin, RR, Medagli, P, Passalacqua, NG, Peccenini, S, Pennesi, R, Pierini, B, Poldini, L, Prosser, F, Raimondo, FM, Roma-Marzio, F, Rosati, L, Santangelo, A, Scoppola, A, Scortegagna, S, Selvaggi, A, Selvi, F, Soldano, A, Stinca, A, Wagensommer, RP, Wilhalm, T, Conti, F, 2018. An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy. Plant Biosystems 152 (2): 179 - 303, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" title="An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" volume="152" year="2018">Bartolucci et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). We confirm here the chromosome number 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 34 previously reported for the species.
</paragraph>
